track.description: A consistent evolution in the meaning of soul, while addicted to bass and riding on pure emotion, Anj Jackson's exhilarating presence behind the decks is a sure-fire way to keep you dancing all night long. Anj Jackson was passionate about music at a very young age, specifically classic rock, alternative, 90's hip-hop, and Much Music's dance mixes. House music legends such as Daftpunk, Mark Farina, and Basement Jaxx exposed her to the underground world of dance music, and she was hooked. Originating from the Great White North in the far northwestern corner of Canada, she is always ready to throw down and brings an attitude that comes standard. Since discovering the decks, you will be hard-pressed to get her off again. Moving more central, Anj found herself immediately involved with local creators and organizers and has since become pervasive in nightclubs and major music festivals across the whole of Western Canada. Her go-to style is rolling bass-line house, on the deeper side, and is currently following artists such as Scott Diaz, Gorgon City, Darius Syrossian, FISHER, Riva Starr, and Kyle Watson. Keep your eyes and ears open for this up-and-coming DJ!
